{"body": "I particularly don't think that Rails should handle developer's mistakes of adding the same field twice to a list of attributes to be validated. If we (as developers) detect the problem (for instance, by seeing duplicated error messages), we can fix it in our code, if we change Rails to ignore the problem, we'll probably never notice the problem exists, and we'll continue doing it over and over.\n\nThanks for your contribution.\n\n*ps: please send new pull requests against the master branch, they'll be backported if needed (unless it's a specific bug that only happens there).*", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/7754549", "created_at": "2012-08-15T12:28:01Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7354#issuecomment-7754549", "updated_at": "2012-08-15T12:28:01Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7354, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "type": "User", "id": 26328, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilv